 interethnic comparisons. As a result the book goes considerably beyond mere demographic description and builds bridges between demography and anthropology or sociology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aculture. 4ademography. 4aethnic studies. 4aminorities. 4apopulation growth. 4apopulation. 4asociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Demography.2bisacsh1 aBledsoe, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelaine, Ghislaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEelens, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaisie, Samuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldman, Noreen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraham, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsiugo-Abanihe, Uche, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaufmann, Georgia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLarsen, Ulla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLesthaeghe, Ron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMbugua, Wariara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeekers, Dominique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPage, Hilary J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPebley, Anne R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPebley, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTimaeus, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVanderhoeft, Camille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe G